SIMPLE: remunerate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Remunerate
<hw>Re*mu"ner*ate</hw> <pr>(-?t)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Remunerated</conjf>
<pr>(-?"t?d)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Remunerating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>remuneratus</ets>,
p. p. of <ets>remunerare</ets>, <ets>remunerari</ets>; pref.
<ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>munerare</ets>, <ets>munerari</ets>, to give,
present, from <ets>munus</ets>, <ets>muneris</ets>, a gift, present. Cf.
<er>Munificent</er>.]</ety> <def>To pay an equivalent to for any
service, loss, expense, or other sacrifice; to recompense; to requite;
<as>as, to <ex>remunerate</ex> men for labor</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To reward; recompense; compensate; satisfy;
requite; repay; pay; reimburse.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Remuneration</ent>⟦br⟧
